def download_adj_close(tickers, start, end):
    data = yf.download(tickers, start=start, end=end, auto_adjust=False, progress=False)['Adj Close']
    # tickerSeriesDataFrame
    if isinstance(data, pd.Series):
        data = data.to_frame()
    return data

# 
prices = download_adj_close(TICKERS, start_date, end_date)
benchmark_prices = download_adj_close([BENCHMARK], start_date, end_date)
risk_free_proxy = yf.download(RISK_FREE_PROXY, start=start_date, end=end_date, auto_adjust=False, progress=False)['Adj Close']

# /
missing_report = prices.isna().sum()
print(':\n', missing_report)

#

# Beta SPY
# 1Beta2Beta60

# 
benchmark_returns = benchmark_all.pct_change().dropna()
benchmark_returns = benchmark_returns.iloc[:, 0]  # SeriesSPY

# 
aligned = returns.join(benchmark_returns.to_frame('SPY'), how='inner')
R = aligned[TICKERS_VALID]
M = aligned['SPY']

# BetaR_i = alpha + beta * M + eps
static_beta = {}
for col in R.columns:
    valid = R[col].dropna().index.intersection(M.dropna().index)
    slope, intercept, r_value, p_value, std_err = linregress(M.loc[valid], R[col].loc[valid])
    static_beta[col] = slope

static_beta = pd.Series(static_beta)
print('BetaSPY\n', static_beta.sort_values(ascending=False).round(2))

# Beta60beta_t = Cov(R_i, M) / Var(M)
window = 60
rolling_beta = pd.DataFrame(index=R.index, columns=R.columns, dtype=float)
var_m = M.rolling(window).var()
for col in R.columns:
    cov_im = R[col].rolling(window).cov(M)
    rolling_beta[col] = cov_im / var_m

# Beta
fig, axes = plt.subplots(len(TICKERS_VALID), 1, figsize=(12, 3*len(TICKERS_VALID)), sharex=True)
if len(TICKERS_VALID) == 1:
    axes = [axes]
for ax, col in zip(axes, TICKERS_VALID):
    rolling_beta[col].plot(ax=ax, title=f'Beta{col} vs SPY, ={window}')
    ax.axhline(static_beta[col], color='red', linestyle='--', alpha=0.6, label='Beta')
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# 
# - 
# - Ledoit-Wolf=1
# - 252N3

from datetime import datetime

# 
rebalance_dates = returns.resample('M').last().index

# 1) 
weights_eq = pd.DataFrame(0.0, index=rebalance_dates, columns=TICKERS_VALID)
weights_eq.loc[:, :] = 1.0 / len(TICKERS_VALID)

# 
w_eq_daily = weights_eq.reindex(returns.index, method='ffill').fillna(method='ffill')
port_eq = (w_eq_daily * returns).sum(axis=1)

# 2) 60
lookback_mv = 60
weights_mv = pd.DataFrame(0.0, index=rebalance_dates, columns=TICKERS_VALID)
for d in rebalance_dates:
    window_returns = returns.loc[returns.index <= d].tail(lookback_mv)
    if window_returns.shape[0] < lookback_mv:
        continue
    # Ledoit-Wolf
    lw = LedoitWolf().fit(window_returns.values)
    cov = lw.covariance_
    # 
    ones = np.ones((cov.shape[0], 1))
    inv_cov = np.linalg.pinv(cov)
    raw_w = inv_cov @ ones
    raw_w = raw_w / (ones.T @ inv_cov @ ones)
    w = np.maximum(raw_w.flatten(), 0)
    w = w / w.sum() if w.sum() > 0 else np.ones_like(w)/len(w)
    weights_mv.loc[d, :] = w

w_mv_daily = weights_mv.reindex(returns.index, method='ffill').fillna(method='ffill')
port_mv = (w_mv_daily * returns).sum(axis=1)

# 3) 2523
lookback_mom = 252
top_n = 3
weights_mom = pd.DataFrame(0.0, index=rebalance_dates, columns=TICKERS_VALID)
for d in rebalance_dates:
    window_returns = returns.loc[:d].tail(lookback_mom)
    if window_returns.shape[0] < lookback_mom:
        continue
    cumret = (1 + window_returns).prod() - 1
    winners = cumret.sort_values(ascending=False).head(top_n).index
    weights_mom.loc[d, winners] = 1.0 / top_n

w_mom_daily = weights_mom.reindex(returns.index, method='ffill').fillna(0.0)
port_mom = (w_mom_daily * returns).sum(axis=1)

# 
portfolio_nav = pd.DataFrame({
    'EQ': (1 + port_eq).cumprod(),
    'MinVar': (1 + port_mv).cumprod(),
    'Momentum': (1 + port_mom).cumprod(),
    'SPY': (1 + benchmark_returns.reindex(returns.index, method='ffill')).cumprod()
}, index=returns.index)

ax = portfolio_nav.plot(title='=1')
ax.set_ylabel('')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# 
def max_drawdown(nav_series: pd.Series) -> float:
    cummax = nav_series.cummax()
    dd = nav_series / cummax - 1
    return dd.min()

perf = {}
for name, nav in portfolio_nav.items():
    ret = nav.pct_change().dropna()
    ann_ret = ret.mean() * 252
    ann_vol = ret.std() * np.sqrt(252)
    sharpe_p = (ann_ret - ann_rf) / (ann_vol + 1e-9)
    mdd = max_drawdown(nav)
    perf[name] = {
        'AnnReturn': ann_ret,
        'AnnVol': ann_vol,
        'Sharpe': sharpe_p,
        'MaxDD': mdd,
    }

perf_df = pd.DataFrame(perf).T
print('\n', perf_df.round(3))
